{% import "_utility.macros.j2" as utility %}
{% import "_slides.macros.j2" as slide %}

{% call slide.wrap('dogs',
  prev='dance',
  next='trans'
  ) %}

  {% call slide.shitz('dogs') %}
    I have more pictures
    {{ utility.link('like this', 'http://images.lmgtfy.com/?q=mating+diagram') }}
    Some of them
    {{ utility.tooltip('involve people.',
      'For the Jazz album by Tadd Dameron and John Coltrane, see %s.'
      % utility.link('Mating Call', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mating_Call') ) }}
    The Internet is a beautiful and strange land.
  {% endcall %}

  <button class="redgreen">
    <span class="is-hidden">Pause/Play</span>
  </button>

  {% call slide.transcript() %}
    {% call slide.p() %}
      Take your time.
      Pause the tape, if needed.
      I can wait.
    {% endcall %}
    {% call slide.p() %}
      Remember:
      Da-Da-Dot, Da-Da-Dot, Da-Da-Dot.
      Da-Da-Dot, Da-Da-Dot, Da-Da-Dot.
    {% endcall %}
    {% call slide.p() %}
      That's morse code for "oooooooo",
      the sound you should make during ritual dances
      inside obsolete book avatar architectures,
      made post-obsolete by their use in rituals
      memorializing the death of books.
      Say "oooooooo", while you dance.
    {% endcall %}
    {% call slide.p() %}
      Or combine the two
      (fast, slow, fast):
      Di-Di-Dit Da-Da-Dot Di-Di-Dit
      sssssssss ooooooooo sssssssss
      an SOS cry for help,
      as the book dies a slow,
      painful, and hideous death.
    {% endcall %}
    {% call slide.p() %}
      You keep dancing,
      and I will read a memorial
      poem in the dead form of a sonnet
      by a dead man.
    {% endcall %}
    <blockquote>
      {% call slide.p() %}
        Death, be not proud, though some have called thee
        Mighty and dreadful, for thou art not so;
        For those whom thou think'st thou dost over throw
        Die not, blah blah blah.
        And dost with poison, war and sickness dwell!
        And so on...
        ...death shall be no more. <b>Death thou shalt die</b>.
      {% endcall %}
      <cite><span>â€” John Donne</span></cite>
    </blockquote>
    {% call slide.p() %}
      Now turn and face the shrine.
    {% endcall %}
  {% endcall %}

{% endcall %}
